quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,We gave Abraham aforetime his rectitude -- for We knew him
  21,52,"when he said to his father and his people, 'What are these statues unto which you are cleaving"
  21,53,"They said, 'We found our fathers serving them"
  21,54,"He said, 'Then assuredly you and your fathers have been in manifest error"
  21,55,"They said, 'What, hast thou come to us with the truth, or art thou one of those that play"
  21,56,"He said, 'Nay, but your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth who originated them, and I am one of those that bear witness thereunto"
  21,57,"And, by God, I shall assuredly outwit your idols, after you have gone away turning your backs"
  21,58,"So he broke them into fragments, all but a great one they had, for haply they would return to it"
  21,59,"They said, 'Who has. done this with our gods? Surely he is one of the evildoers"
  21,60,"They said, 'We heard a young man making mention of them, and he was called Abraham"
  21,61,"They said, 'Bring him before the people's eyes; haply they shall bear witness"
  21,62,"They said, 'So, art thou the man who did this unto our gods, Abraham"
  21,63,"He said, 'No; it was this great one of them that did it. Question them; if they are able to speak"
  21,64,"So they returned one to another, and they said, 'Surely it is you who are the evildoers"
  21,65,"Then they were utterly put to confusion saying, 'Very well indeed thou knowest these do not speak"
  21,66,"He said, 'What, and do you serve, apart from God, that which profits you nothing; neither hurts you"
  21,67,Fie upon you and that you serve apart from God! Do you not understand
  21,68,"They said, 'Burn him, and help your gods, if you would do aught"
  21,69,"We said, 'O fire, be coolness and safety for Abraham"
  21,70,They desired to outwit him; so We made them the worse losers
  21,71,"and We delivered him, and Lot, unto the land that We had blessed for all beings"
  21,72,"And We gave him Isaac and Jacob in superfluity, and every one made We righteous"
  21,73,"and appointed them to be leaders guiding by Our command, and We revealed to them the doing of good deeds, and to perform the prayer, and to pay the alms, and Us they served"
  21,74,"And Lot -- to him We gave judgment and knowledge; and we delivered him from the city that had been doing deeds of corruption; they were an evil people, truly ungodly"
  21,75,and We admitted him into Our mercy; he was of the righteous
  21,76,"And Noah -- when he called before, and We answered him, and delivered him and his people from the great distress"
  21,77,"and We helped him against the people who cried lies to Our signs; surely they were an evil people, so We drowned them all together"
  21,78,"And David and Solomon -- when they gave judgment concerning the tillage, when the sheep of the people strayed there, and We bore witness to their judgment"
  21,79,"and We made Solomon to understand it, and unto each gave We judgment and knowledge. And with David We subjected the mountains to give glory, and the birds, and We were doers"
  21,80,"And We taught him the fashioning of garments for you, to fortify you against your violence; then are you thankful"
  21,81,"And to Solomon the wind, strongly blowing, that ran at his command unto the land that We had blessed; and We had knowledge of everything"
  21,82,and of the Satans some dived for him and did other work besides; and We were watching over them